  "prompt": "Is Sri Ramakrishna Paramahamsa an avatar?",
  "response": "Sri Ramakrishna Paramahamsa is considered by many of his followers and admirers to be an avatar, which in Hinduism means an incarnation of a deity, often Vishnu. He was a 19th-century Indian mystic and saint, and his spiritual teachings have had a significant influence on Hinduism. His devotees believe that he embodied divine qualities and had direct experiences of God in various forms, including as Kali, Rama, Krishna, and others.\n\nHowever, whether someone is an avatar is a matter of personal belief and religious interpretation. Different people and traditions may have varying opinions on this matter.",
